<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1075,1604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,1255,1280]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[406,515,1255,1279]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1847,1870]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1823]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Belciades spp., imagines. 1, 2 – B. niveola (1 – Russian Far East, 2 – Korea); 3, 4 – B. koenigi, China (3 – holotype), 5, 6 – B. hoenei, China, (5 – holotype, 6 – paratype); 7, 8 – B. sugii (7 – Thailand, 8 – China)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203317/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
Figs. 
<number box="[470,515,1255,1279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" value="3.4">3, 4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[656,780,1255,1280]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.05" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="40.5" valueMax="42.0" valueMin="39.0">39–42 mm</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[791,906,1256,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koenigi">
<emphasis box="[791,906,1256,1280]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">B. koenigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is externally similar in color and pattern of the forewing to B. 
<taxonomicName box="[323,405,1292,1316]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveola">
<emphasis box="[323,405,1292,1316]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">niveola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in more intensive cyan-bluish-green tint of ground color of forewing and grayish-brown hindwing with two traceable pale transverse lines. In forewing pattern it differs in shape of basal band, absence of white border around inner and outer lines and less expressed grey suffusion in medial field. In male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[222,303,1399,1423]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1774,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1753]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Belciades spp., male genitalia. 17 – B. niveola, Russian Far East, genit. prep. 1641 ZFMK; 18 – B. koenigi, paratype, China, genit. prep. 1641 ZFMK; 19 – B. hoenei, paratype, genit. prep. 1639 ZFMK; 20 – B. sugii, Thailand, genit. prep. 7277 GB." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203319/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[274,303,1399,1423]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) it differs mainly by more proportional shape of valva (the neck of cucullus less expressed), shape of juxta and completely reduced harpe. The vesica is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[916,999,1436,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Belciades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveola">
<emphasis box="[916,999,1436,1460]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">niveola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing by the absence of cornuti on basal part (a row of spines is on ventral lobe of carina). The female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1031,1113,1472,1496]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 26" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1841,1864]" captionTargetBox="[188,1415,194,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1821]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 26. Belciades spp., male and female genitalia. 21 – B. cyana, male genitalia, paratype, China, HHL- 1964 - 1; 22 – B. cyanobrunnea, male genitalia, holotype, Thailand, genit. prep. 7410 GB; 23 – B. niveola female genitalia, Russian Far East, genit. prep. 1641 ZFMK; 24 – B. koenigi female genitalia 1160 ZFMK; 25 – B. hoenei female genitalia, genit. prep. 1652 ZFMK; 26 – B. cyanobrunnea, paratype, female genitalia, China, Jianxi / Fujian, 7408 GB." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203320/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[1084,1113,1472,1496]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
) have prominent differences in shape of ostial part: antrum oval, without the folk-like antevaginal plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="42" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1075,1604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,497,1543,1568]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">Distribution and biology.</emphasis>
